-- German Imports More Crude as Prices Rise, Economy Ministry Says
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-05-09T10:00:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/german-imports-more-crude-as-prices-rise-economy-ministry-says.html
German crude oil imports increased by
4.4 percent to 7.2 million metric tons in March, according to
data from Economy Ministry.  Imports in the first quarter rose 2.7 percent to 22.4
million tons as  Russia , the U.K. and Norway were the biggest
suppliers, the ministry said today in an e-mailed statement.
